Thorax. Antepronotal lobes with V-shaped notch (
Fig. 5
) and with 2–3 lateral setae. Acrostichals 12–17 , beginning close to antepronotum (
1 specimen
) or some distance from antepronotum (
3 specimens
) (
Fig. 4
), dorsocentrals 8–12 , prealars 3–4 . Scutellum with 6–9 setae.

Wing. R with 11–15 setae, R 1 with 3–5 setae, R 4 + 5 with 2–5 setae subapically. Costa extension 56–68 µm. Anal lobe rounded. Squama with 3–5 setae (
Fig. 7
).

